      "raw_text": "Following instructions from the\nspecial meeting of the city council\nlast night. the councils committee on\nstreets visited the viaduct under the\nNorthern Pacific tracks on Washing\nton street this morning to consult\nwith adjoining property owners and\nestimate the amount of excavating\nthat woGid be necessary to permit the\ntrolley cars of the Spokane Traction\ncompany to pass under the tracks.\n\n\nThe committee was informed that\nthe present grade of the street is\nabout one foot and half higher than\nnormal, and that an extra three feet\nwill have to be excavated to give the\nstreet car company much space\nas Is desired under the railroad\ntracks.\n\n\n1t was agreed by we committee to\nhave Engineer Gill prepare plans"
    }
